  "text": "Kafka consumer offset management is implemented through several key components:\n\n**Offset Storage and Metadata:**\n- `org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/OffsetAndMetadata.java` and `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetAndMetadata.java` define the structure for storing offset along with associated metadata\n- `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java` manages the lifecycle of committed offsets including commit, fetch, and retention\n- `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetExpirationCondition.java` and `OffsetExpirationConditionImpl.java` handle offset expiry logic based on retention policies\n\n**Group Coordinator and Offset Commit Handling:**\n- `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinator.java` is the main interface for coordinator operations including commitOffsets and fetchOffsets\n- `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java` handles requests for a specific partition of the __consumer_offsets topic\n- `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupMetadataManager.java` manages group metadata and delegates offset operations\n- `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/Group.java` and its implementations (ClassicGroup, ConsumerGroup) track group state and committed offsets\n- `org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java` provides serialization helpers for offset commit records\n\n**Request/Response Processing:**\n- `kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala` contains handleOffsetCommitRequest, handleOffsetFetchRequest, and handleTxnOffsetCommitRequest methods that route requests to the coordinator\n- `org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetCommitRequest.java` and OffsetCommitResponse.java define the protocol for offset commit operations\n- `org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetFetchRequest.java` and OffsetFetchResponse.java define the protocol for offset fetch operations\n- `org/apache/kafka/common/requests/TxnOffsetCommitRequest.java` and TxnOffsetCommitResponse.java handle transactional offset commits\n\n**Client-Side Offset Management:**\n- `org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CommitRequestManager.java` manages offset commit requests on the client side\n- `org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/OffsetFetcher.java` fetches committed offsets and manages offset state\n- `org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java` coordinates with the broker-side coordinator\n\n**Admin APIs:**\n- Various admin classes handle listing, altering, and deleting consumer group offsets through APIs\n\n**Offset Storage (Internal):**\n- `kafka/coordinator/group/CoordinatorPartitionWriter.scala` writes offset commit records to the __consumer_offsets topic partition\n- `kafka/coordinator/group/CoordinatorLoaderImpl.scala` loads offset metadata from __consumer_offsets during startup using the CoordinatorLoader interface\n- `kafka/coordinator/transaction/TransactionCoordinator.scala` and TransactionStateManager.scala handle offsets in transactional contexts\n\nThe architecture uses a central __consumer_offsets topic where all offset commits are appended, with the CoordinatorLoaderImpl reading these records during startup to rebuild the in-memory offset state for each consumer group."
